#: ../../../reference/random/generated/numpy.random.Generator.multivariate_normal.rst:4
msgid "numpy.random.Generator.multivariate\\_normal"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/random/generated/numpy.random.Generator.multivariate_normal.rst:8
msgid "method"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.multivariate_normal:2
msgid "Draw random samples from a multivariate normal distribution."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.multivariate_normal:4
msgid ""
"The multivariate normal, multinormal or Gaussian distribution is a "
"generalization of the one-dimensional normal distribution to higher "
"dimensions.  Such a distribution is specified by its mean and covariance "
"matrix.  These parameters are analogous to the mean (average or \"center\") "
"and variance (the squared standard deviation, or \"width\") of the one-"
"dimensional normal distribution."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.multivariate_normal:0
msgid "Parameters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.multivariate_normal:14
msgid "**mean**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.multivariate_normal:-1
msgid "1-D array_like, of length N"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.multivariate_normal:14
msgid "Mean of the N-dimensional distribution."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.multivariate_normal:18
msgid "**cov**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.multivariate_normal:-1
msgid "2-D array_like, of shape (N, N)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.multivariate_normal:17
msgid ""
"Covariance matrix of the distribution. It must be symmetric and positive-"
"semidefinite for proper sampling."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.multivariate_normal:24
msgid "**size**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.multivariate_normal:-1
msgid "int or tuple of ints, optional"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.multivariate_normal:21
msgid ""
"Given a shape of, for example, ``(m,n,k)``, ``m*n*k`` samples are generated, "
"and packed in an `m`-by-`n`-by-`k` arrangement.  Because each sample is `N`-"
"dimensional, the output shape is ``(m,n,k,N)``. If no shape is specified, a "
"single (`N`-D) sample is returned."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.multivariate_normal:27
msgid "**check_valid**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.multivariate_normal:-1
msgid "{ 'warn', 'raise', 'ignore' }, optional"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.multivariate_normal:27
msgid "Behavior when the covariance matrix is not positive semidefinite."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.multivariate_normal:31
msgid "**tol**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.multivariate_normal:-1
msgid "float, optional"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.multivariate_normal:30
msgid ""
"Tolerance when checking the singular values in covariance matrix. cov is "
"cast to double before the check."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.multivariate_normal:41
msgid "**method**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.multivariate_normal:-1
msgid "{ 'svd', 'eigh', 'cholesky'}, optional"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.multivariate_normal:34
msgid ""
"The cov input is used to compute a factor matrix A such that ``A @ A.T = "
"cov``. This argument is used to select the method used to compute the factor "
"matrix A. The default method 'svd' is the slowest, while 'cholesky' is the "
"fastest but less robust than the slowest method. The method `eigh` uses "
"eigen decomposition to compute A and is faster than svd but slower than "
"cholesky."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.multivariate_normal:0
msgid "Returns"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.multivariate_normal:57
msgid "**out**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.multivariate_normal:-1
msgid "ndarray"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.multivariate_normal:46
msgid ""
"The drawn samples, of shape *size*, if that was provided.  If not, the shape "
"is ``(N,)``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.multivariate_normal:49
msgid ""
"In other words, each entry ``out[i,j,...,:]`` is an N-dimensional value "
"drawn from the distribution."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.multivariate_normal:60
msgid "Notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.multivariate_normal:61
msgid ""
"The mean is a coordinate in N-dimensional space, which represents the "
"location where samples are most likely to be generated.  This is analogous "
"to the peak of the bell curve for the one-dimensional or univariate normal "
"distribution."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.multivariate_normal:66
msgid ""
"Covariance indicates the level to which two variables vary together. From "
"the multivariate normal distribution, we draw N-dimensional samples, :math:"
"`X = [x_1, x_2, ..., x_N]`.  The covariance matrix element :math:`C_{ij}` is "
"the covariance of :math:`x_i` and :math:`x_j`. The element :math:`C_{ii}` is "
"the variance of :math:`x_i` (i.e. its \"spread\")."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.multivariate_normal:73
msgid ""
"Instead of specifying the full covariance matrix, popular approximations "
"include:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.multivariate_normal:76
msgid "Spherical covariance (`cov` is a multiple of the identity matrix)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.multivariate_normal:77
msgid ""
"Diagonal covariance (`cov` has non-negative elements, and only on the "
"diagonal)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.multivariate_normal:80
msgid ""
"This geometrical property can be seen in two dimensions by plotting "
"generated data-points:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.multivariate_normal:86
msgid ""
"Diagonal covariance means that the variables are independent, and the "
"probability density contours have their axes aligned with the coordinate "
"axes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.multivariate_normal:96
msgid ""
"Note that the covariance matrix must be positive semidefinite (a.k.a. "
"nonnegative-definite). Otherwise, the behavior of this method is undefined "
"and backwards compatibility is not guaranteed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.multivariate_normal:100
msgid ""
"This function internally uses linear algebra routines, and thus results may "
"not be identical (even up to precision) across architectures, OSes, or even "
"builds. For example, this is likely if ``cov`` has multiple equal singular "
"values and ``method`` is ``'svd'`` (default). In this case, "
"``method='cholesky'`` may be more robust."
msgstr ""

